:title("JavaScript to LLVM IR compiler") ;
:description("Compiles normal, dynamically typed JavaScript to an LLVM IR module and runs it
with the built-in IR interpreter.

The language is exactly the one of js-interpreter.abnf; see there for a description
(including the bitwise operators and assignment targets that reach through calls). Unlike
MetaJS, variables are NOT type pinned: declarations and assignments go through the
UNPINNED scope externals js_scope_decl / js_scope_set / js_scope_get, so a variable can
hold values of any type over its lifetime.

The emitted IR is handle threaded code: every dynamic value is an i64 handle into the
value table of the Go side JS runtime (abnf/jsrt.go), and every operation with real
JS semantics is a call to one of its js_* externals (js_add, js_get, js_call, ...).
Only the control flow is real IR: if/while/for/&&/||/?: compile to basic blocks,
branches and phis, driven by js_truthy. The handles 0..3 are the constants undefined,
null, false and true. Variables live in scope chain objects on the host side
(js_scope_new, js_scope_get, and the declaring/assigning js_scope_decl/js_scope_set),
and the scope chain is what gives closures their captured
environment: a function expression becomes an own IR function jsf_N(env, args) plus a
js_closure(N, currentScope) at the site of its creation. String and number literals
enter through module globals (js_str_mem) and js_num_i/js_num_str.

Every tag composes a small code generator function (a 'thunk') out of the thunks of its
children. Expression thunks get the current basic block and return {b: endBlock,
v: handle value}; statement thunks get the current block and return the block that the
following code has to continue in (short circuit operators and loops branch, so both
can move the insertion point). The top level becomes the function jsmain(env, args),
which runs the program statements and then calls main().

The exit code of the metacompiler run is the value that main() returns, so the test
programs are self checking: they return 0 on success.
The same language with the same semantics is interpreted directly by js-interpreter.abnf.

A plain `=` assignment to a name that was never declared becomes an implicit global
(created in the root scope) through js_scope_set_or_create, matching the non-strict
JavaScript semantics of js-interpreter.abnf. A compound assignment (+=, ++, ...) reads
the old value first and so still requires a prior var/let/const declaration.") ;


// --- main rules

// Shared token productions (languages/lib).
:include("lib/cstyle-comments.abnf") ;
:include("lib/ident-dollar.abnf") ;
:include("lib/dq-strings.abnf") ;
:include("lib/numbers.abnf") ;
:include("lib/bools.abnf") ;

:startRule(Program) ;
:whitespace(Whitespace) ;

// The merged statement thunks of the top level become jsmain(env, args) in the module.
Program     <~~ buildMain(takeAll()) ~~>
            = { Statement } ;

// Every statement production pushes exactly one thunk: function() -> undefined | signal.
Statement   <~~ push(stmtPos(pop())) ~~>
            = Block | ImportStmt | ExportStmt | ClassDecl | TryStmt | Destructure | VarDecl | If | While | Do | ForOf | For | Switch | Return | Break | Continue
            | Throw | Debugger | With | AsyncFuncDecl | GenFuncDecl | FuncDecl | Empty | ExprStmt ;

// The JS switch: === comparison, fallthrough until break, stacked labels, default
// anywhere. The body is a flat list - the labels must be tried before Statement,
// because 'case 1:' would otherwise parse as two expression statements (semicolons
// are optional).
Switch      <~~ push(makeSwitch(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwSwitch "(" Expression ")" "{" { CaseLabel | DefaultLabel | Statement } "}" ;
CaseLabel   <~~ push({casev: pop()}) ~~>
            = KwCase AssignExpr ":" ;
DefaultLabel <~~ push({isdflt: true}) ~~>
            = KwDefault ":" ;

Block       <~~ push(makeBlockStmt(takeAll())) ~~>
            = "{" { Statement } "}" ;

// var, let and const all declare a block scoped variable in the current scope.
VarDecl     = VarDeclCore [ ";" ] ;
VarDeclCore <~~ push(makeSeq(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwVar Declarator { "," Declarator } ;
Declarator  <~~ push(makeDecl(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> [ "=" AssignExpr ] ;

// [condThunk, thenThunk] or [condThunk, thenThunk, elseThunk].
If          <~~ push(makeIf(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwIf "(" Expression ")" Statement [ KwElse Statement ] ;

While       <~~ push(makeWhile(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = KwWhile "(" Expression ")" Statement ;

Do          <~~ push(makeDo(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = KwDo Statement KwWhile "(" Expression ")" [ ";" ] ;

// The three optional parts are wrapped with a kind marker, otherwise e.g.
// 'for (;c;)' and 'for (i=0;;)' could not be told apart on the stack.
For         <~~ push(makeFor(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwFor "(" [ ForInit ] ";" [ ForCond ] ";" [ ForPost ] ")" Statement ;
ForInit     <~~ push({k:"init", t:pop()}) ~~> = ForVar | ForExpr ;
ForVar      = VarDeclCore ;
ForExpr     <~~ push(exprToClause(pop())) ~~> = Expression ;
ForCond     <~~ push({k:"cond", t:pop()}) ~~> = Expression ;
ForPost     <~~ push({k:"post", t:exprToClause(pop())}) ~~> = Expression ;

// [] or [exprThunk].
Return      <~~ push(makeReturn(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwReturn [ Expression ] [ ";" ] ;

Break       <~~ push(makeBreak()) ~~>
            = KwBreak [ ";" ] ;

Continue    <~~ push(makeContinue()) ~~>
            = KwContinue [ ";" ] ;

Throw       <~~ push(makeThrow(pop())) ~~>
            = KwThrow Expression [ ";" ] ;

// A function declaration binds the closure in the current scope when it executes.
FuncDecl    <~~ push(makeFuncDecl(pop(), pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = KwFunction Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ParamList Block ;

ParamList   <~~ push(takeAll()) /* Collect the parameter names into one array. */ ~~>
            = "(" [ Param { "," Param } [ "," ] ] ")" ;

// A parameter: a plain name (genuine), or a default/rest parameter, which are ACCEPTED
// (the bare name is still bound) but fire notImplemented for the dropped default/rest.
Param       = RestParam | DefaultParam | PlainParam ;
PlainParam  <~~ push(up.in) ~~>
            = Id ;
DefaultParam <~~ pop(); notImpl("default parameter", up.pos) ~~>
            = Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> "=" AssignExpr ;
RestParam   <~~ notImpl("rest parameter", up.pos) ~~>
            = "..." Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ;

Empty       <~~ push(function(b) { return b }) ~~>
            = ";" ;

ExprStmt    <~~ push(exprToStmt(pop())) ~~>
            = Expression [ ";" ] ;

// Every expression production pushes exactly one thunk: function(block) -> {b, v}.
Expression  = AssignExpr ;

// Assignment is an expression and associates to the right: a = b = c.
// If the assignment shape does not fit (e.g. 'a == b'), the parser falls back to CondExpr.
AssignExpr  = Assignment | AssignExtended | Yield | CondExpr ;
Assignment  <~~ push(makeAssign(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Target ( "+=" | "-=" | "*=" | "/=" | "%=" | "=" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> AssignExpr ;

// The extended compound assignments (** <<  >> >>> & ^ | && || ?? forms) and yield are
// accepted but not lowered; the longer operators are tried before their prefixes.
AssignExtended <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplExpr("compound assignment", up.pos)) ~~>
            = Target ( "**=" | ">>>=" | "<<=" | ">>=" | "&&=" | "||=" | "??=" | "&=" | "^=" | "|=" ) AssignExpr ;
Yield       <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplExpr("yield expression", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwYield [ "*" ] [ AssignExpr ] ;

// An assignable place: a variable, or a member path that may reach through calls
// but must end in a member: findScope(name)[name] = value.
// The local stack holds [name, suffix marker, suffix marker, ...].
Target      <~~ push(makeTargetRef(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> { CallSuffix | DotSuffix | IndexSuffix } ;

CondExpr    <~~ push(makeCond(takeAll())) ~~>
            = NullishExpr [ "?" AssignExpr ":" AssignExpr ] ;

// Nullish coalescing sits just under the ternary; it is accepted but not lowered.
// With no "??" it is a transparent pass-through of its single operand.
NullishExpr <~~ push(makeNullish(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = OrExpr { "??" OrExpr } ;

OrExpr      <~~ push(makeOrAnd(takeAll(), true)) ~~>
            = AndExpr { "||" AndExpr } ;

AndExpr     <~~ push(makeOrAnd(takeAll(), false)) ~~>
            = BitOrExpr { "&&" BitOrExpr } ;

// The bitwise levels sit between && and equality, like in JS. A single "|" that
// actually starts a "||" fails its right side, the iteration rolls back, and the
// enclosing || level picks it up.
BitOrExpr   <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = BitXorExpr { "|" <~~ push("|") ~~> BitXorExpr } ;
BitXorExpr  <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = BitAndExpr { "^" <~~ push("^") ~~> BitAndExpr } ;
BitAndExpr  <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = EqExpr { "&" <~~ push("&") ~~> EqExpr } ;

// The longer operators must be tried before their prefixes ("===" before "==").
EqExpr      <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = InExpr { ( "===" | "!==" | "==" | "!=" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> InExpr } ;

// The 'instanceof' and 'in' relational operators are accepted but not lowered
// (no prototype chain / key-membership model in the subset). With neither operator
// present this level is a transparent pass-through.
InExpr      <~~ push(makeInInstanceof(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = RelExpr { ( KwInstanceof | KwIn ) <~~ push("op") ~~> RelExpr } ;

RelExpr     <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = ShiftExpr { ( "<=" | ">=" | "<" | ">" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ShiftExpr } ;

ShiftExpr   <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = AddExpr { ( "<<" | ">>>" | ">>" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> AddExpr } ;

AddExpr     <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = MulExpr { ( "+" | "-" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> MulExpr } ;

MulExpr     <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = ExpExpr { ( "*" | "/" | "%" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ExpExpr } ;

// Exponentiation binds tighter than the multiplicatives; accepted but not lowered.
// With no "**" it is a transparent pass-through of its single operand.
ExpExpr     <~~ push(makeExp(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = UnaryExpr { "**" UnaryExpr } ;

UnaryExpr   = PreIncDec | Neg | Not | BitNot | Typeof | Delete | Void | Await | PostfixExpr ;
// delete, void and await are accepted but not lowered.
Delete      <~~ pop(); push(notImplExpr("delete operator", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwDelete UnaryExpr ;
Void        <~~ pop(); push(notImplExpr("void operator", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwVoid UnaryExpr ;
Await       <~~ pop(); push(notImplExpr("await expression", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwAwait UnaryExpr ;
// Prefix ++/--: the expression value is the new one.
PreIncDec   <~~ push(makePreIncDec(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = ( "++" | "--" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> Target ;
Neg         <~~ push(makeUnary(pop(), "js_neg")) ~~>
            = "-" UnaryExpr ;
Not         <~~ push(makeUnary(pop(), "js_not")) ~~>
            = "!" UnaryExpr ;
BitNot      <~~ push(makeBitNot(pop())) ~~>
            = "~" UnaryExpr ;
Typeof      <~~ push(makeUnary(pop(), "js_typeof")) ~~>
            = KwTypeof UnaryExpr ;

// The postfix forms: i++ evaluates to the old value.
PostfixExpr = IncDec | SuperCall | CallMember ;
IncDec      <~~ push(makeIncDec(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Target ( "++" | "--" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ;

// super(args) delegates to the parent constructor; super.m(args) invokes the parent's
// method on 'this'. popName pulls the optional '.m' out, leaving the argument thunks.
SuperCall   <~~ push(makeSuperCall(popName(), takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwSuper [ "." Id <~~ push({mname: up.in}) ~~> ] "(" [ Arg { "," Arg } [ "," ] ] ")" ;

// A primary expression followed by any mix of calls and member accesses: a.b[i](x).c().
// A call after a member access is a method call: the object becomes 'this' of the callee.
// An optional-chaining suffix (?. ?.[ ?.( ) is accepted but routes the whole chain to
// notImplemented (no short-circuit-on-nullish model in the subset).
CallMember  <~~ push(foldCallMember(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Primary { CallSuffix | DotSuffix | IndexSuffix | OptChainSuffix } ;
CallSuffix  <~~ push({kind:"call", args: takeAll()}) ~~>
            = "(" [ Arg { "," Arg } [ "," ] ] ")" ;
DotSuffix   = "." Id <~~ push({kind:"member", key: makeConst(up.in)}) ~~> ;
IndexSuffix <~~ push({kind:"member", key: pop()}) ~~>
            = "[" Expression "]" ;
OptChainSuffix <~~ takeAll(); push({kind:"optchain", pos: up.pos}) ~~>
            = "?." ( CallSuffix | IndexSuffix | Id ) ;

// A call/array/new argument; the spread form (...expr) is accepted but not lowered.
Arg         = SpreadElem | AssignExpr ;
SpreadElem  <~~ pop(); push(notImplExpr("spread element", up.pos)) ~~>
            = "..." AssignExpr ;

Primary     = AsyncArrow | ArrowFn | NewTarget | NewExpr | "(" Expression ")" | AsyncFuncExpr | GenFuncExpr | FunctionExpr | ClassExpr
            | TemplateLit | RegexLit | ObjectLit | ArrayLit | StringLit | NumberLit
            | True | False | Null | Undefined | VarRef ;

// new C(args): build an instance of the class named C. Member/call suffixes may follow
// (new C().m()).
NewExpr     <~~ push(makeNew(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwNew Id <~~ push({cls: up.in}) ~~> "(" [ Arg { "," Arg } [ "," ] ] ")" ;

// new.target, async arrows, async/generator function expressions and class expressions
// are all accepted but not lowered.
NewTarget   <~~ push(notImplExpr("new.target", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwNew "." "target" KwEnd ;
AsyncArrow  <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplExpr("async arrow function", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwAsync ArrowParams "=>" ArrowBody ;
AsyncFuncExpr <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplExpr("async function expression", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwAsync KwFunction [ "*" ] [ Id ] ParamList Block ;
GenFuncExpr <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplExpr("generator function expression", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwFunction "*" [ Id ] ParamList Block ;
ClassExpr   <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplExpr("class expression", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwClass [ KwExtends Id | Id [ KwExtends Id ] ] "{" { ClassMember } "}" ;

// The optional name of a function expression is accepted but not bound.
FunctionExpr <~~ push(makeFunctionExpr(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = KwFunction [ Id ] ParamList Block ;

// The object literal accepts, besides the genuine `key: value` form, the modern
// property forms - spread, computed keys, getters/setters, shorthand methods (incl.
// async/generator) and shorthand names - each ACCEPTED and routed to notImplemented.
ObjectLit   <~~ push(makeObject(takeAll())) ~~>
            = "{" [ ObjMember { "," ObjMember } [ "," ] ] "}" ;
ObjMember   = SpreadProp | ComputedProp | GetSetProp | MethodProp | PropDef | ShorthandProp ;
PropDef     <~~ push(makeProp(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = PropKey ":" AssignExpr ;
PropKey     = Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> | StringLit ;
SpreadProp  <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplProp("object spread", up.pos)) ~~>
            = "..." AssignExpr ;
ComputedProp <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplProp("computed property", up.pos)) ~~>
            = "[" Expression "]" ( ":" AssignExpr | ParamList Block ) ;
GetSetProp  <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplProp("accessor property", up.pos)) ~~>
            = ( "get" | "set" ) KwEnd PropKey ParamList Block ;
MethodProp  <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplProp("method property", up.pos)) ~~>
            = [ "async" KwEnd ] [ "*" ] PropKey ParamList Block ;
ShorthandProp <~~ push(notImplProp("shorthand property", up.pos)) ~~>
            = Id ;

ArrayLit    <~~ push(makeArray(takeAll())) ~~>
            = "[" [ Arg { "," Arg } [ "," ] ] "]" ;

// Arrow functions: x => x+1, (a, b) => a+b, () => { ... }. They reuse the same
// closure machinery (emitFunction/js_closure) as function expressions; an expression
// body is an implicit 'return <expr>'. Tried before "(" Expression ")" and VarRef.
ArrowFn     <~~ push(makeArrow(takeAll())) ~~>
            = ArrowParams "=>" ArrowBody ;
ArrowParams <~~ push({aparams: takeAll()}) ~~>
            = "(" [ Param { "," Param } [ "," ] ] ")"
            | Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ;
ArrowBody   = ArrowBlock | ArrowExpr ;
ArrowBlock  <~~ push({body: pop()}) ~~>  = Block ;
ArrowExpr   <~~ push({ebody: pop()}) ~~> = AssignExpr ;

// Template literals: `text ${expr} more`. Each ${...} is evaluated and coerced to
// string (js_add); the result is always a string. Whitespace is disabled inside the
// backticks and re-enabled inside a ${...}. A lone '$' is a literal character.
TemplateLit <~~ push(makeTemplate(takeAll())) ~~>
            = "`" :whitespace() { TplExpr | TplChars | TplDollar } "`" :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
TplExpr     <~~ push({expr: pop()}) ~~>
            = "${" :whitespace(Whitespace) Expression "}" ;
TplChars    <~~ push({str: unescapeJs(up.in)}) ~~>
            = TplChar { TplChar } ;
TplChar     = TplEsc | TplPlain ;
TplEsc      = "\\" "\x00"..."\U0010ffff" ;
TplPlain    = "\x00"..."\x23" | "\x25"..."\x5b" | "\x5d"..."\x5f" | "\x61"..."\U0010ffff" ;
TplDollar   <~~ push({str: "$"}) ~~>
            = "$" ;

// for-of over an array or string iterates its elements/characters (genuine).
// for-in is not implemented (host key enumeration is an off-limits extern);
// under -warn-unsupported its iterable is evaluated and the body skipped.
ForOf       <~~ push(makeForOf(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwFor "(" [ KwVar ] Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~>
              ( KwOf | KwIn ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> Expression ")" Statement ;

// A destructuring binding: var [a, b] = xs, var {x, y: alias} = o, and nested
// combinations of the two. The pattern is reified on the stack (arr/obj/id nodes)
// and lowered by makeDestructure: the initializer runs once, then every leaf name
// is declared with js_scope_decl to its array element (js_get by index) or object
// property (js_get by key). The interpreter grammar mirrors this exactly.
Destructure <~~ push(makeDestructure(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwVar DPattern "=" AssignExpr [ ";" ] ;
DPattern    = ArrPattern | ObjPattern ;
ArrPattern  <~~ push({dtype: "arr", elems: takeAll()}) ~~>
            = "[" [ DElem { "," DElem } ] "]" ;
ObjPattern  <~~ push({dtype: "obj", fields: takeAll()}) ~~>
            = "{" [ DField { "," DField } ] "}" ;
DElem       = DIdElem | DPattern ;
DIdElem     <~~ push({dtype: "id", name: up.in}) ~~>
            = Id ;
DField      <~~ push(makeDField(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> [ ":" DElem ] ;

// try/catch/finally and throw are implemented: throw calls js_throw, each try/catch/
// finally body compiles to its own closure handed to js_try, and a return/break/
// continue leaving a try or catch body becomes a control signal that excDispatch
// re-issues in the enclosing frame. The catch binding is optional (ES2019 catch {}).
TryStmt     <~~ push(makeTry(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwTry TryBody [ CatchClause ] [ FinallyClause ] ;
TryBody     <~~ push({trybody: pop()}) ~~>
            = Block ;
CatchClause <~~ push(makeCatch(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwCatch [ "(" Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ")" ] Block ;
FinallyClause <~~ push({finbody: pop()}) ~~>
            = KwFinally Block ;

// A class declaration: fields, a constructor and instance/static methods lower to the
// shared __class machinery (an instance is js_obj_new carrying a __class descriptor that
// holds the methods; a method call dispatches through js_mcall, super through
// js_supercall). An instance is a plain object; static members live on the descriptor.
ClassDecl   <~~ push(makeClassStmt(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwClass Id <~~ push({cname: up.in}); curClassName = up.in ~~>
              [ KwExtends Id <~~ push({ext: up.in}) ~~> ]
              "{" { ClassMember } "}" ;

// The members: a constructor, methods and fields (tried in that order so 'constructor'
// and a method's '(' are recognized before the field form). A stray ';' is skipped.
// The modern member forms (static block, accessors, async/generator/computed/private
// methods and fields) are ACCEPTED and routed to notImplemented (they push a skip
// marker so makeClassStmt ignores them).
ClassMember = ClassSemi | ClassStaticBlock | CtorDef | ClassGetSet | ClassSpecialMethod | ClassPrivate | ClassComputed | MethodDef | FieldDef ;
ClassSemi   <~~ push({skip: true}) ~~> = ";" ;
ClassStaticBlock <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplMember("static block", up.pos)) ~~>
            = "static" KwEnd Block ;
ClassGetSet <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplMember("accessor member", up.pos)) ~~>
            = MemberMods ( "get" | "set" ) KwEnd PropKey ParamList Block ;
ClassSpecialMethod <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplMember("async/generator method", up.pos)) ~~>
            = MemberMods ( "async" KwEnd [ "*" ] | "*" ) PropKey ParamList Block ;
ClassPrivate <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplMember("private member", up.pos)) ~~>
            = MemberMods "#" Id ( ParamList Block | [ "=" AssignExpr ] [ ";" ] ) ;
ClassComputed <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplMember("computed member", up.pos)) ~~>
            = MemberMods "[" Expression "]" ( ParamList Block | [ "=" AssignExpr ] [ ";" ] ) ;

// A constructor.
CtorDef     <~~ push(makeCtor(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwConstructor CtorParams Block ;
CtorParams  <~~ push(takeAll()) ~~>
            = "(" [ Param { "," Param } [ "," ] ] ")" ;

// A method (instance unless 'static').
MethodDef   <~~ push(makeMethod(takeAll())) ~~>
            = MemberMods Id <~~ push({mname: up.in}) ~~> ParamList Block ;

// A field (instance unless 'static'), with an optional initializer.
FieldDef    <~~ push(makeField(takeAll())) ~~>
            = MemberMods Id <~~ push({fname: up.in}) ~~> [ "=" AssignExpr ] [ ";" ] ;

MemberMods  <~~ push({mods: takeAll()}) ~~>
            = { MemberMod <~~ push(up.in) ~~> } ;
MemberMod   = "static" KwEnd ;

// ----- Widened statement surface (ACCEPTED, routed to notImplemented) -----

// ES module import/export. The clause shapes are parsed structurally and dropped;
// there is no module loader in the subset (imports for the other languages resolve
// against a stdlib set; this dynamic dialect has none).
ImportStmt  <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplStmt("import statement", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwImport ( ImportClause KwFrom StringLit | StringLit ) [ ";" ] ;
ImportClause = ImportBinding [ "," ImportTail ] | ImportTail ;
ImportBinding = Id ;
ImportTail  = ImportNs | ImportNamed ;
ImportNs    = "*" KwAs Id ;
ImportNamed = "{" [ ImportSpec { "," ImportSpec } [ "," ] ] "}" ;
ImportSpec  = ( Id | StringLit ) [ KwAs Id ] ;

ExportStmt  <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplStmt("export statement", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwExport ( ExportAll | ExportNamed [ KwFrom StringLit ] | KwDefault AssignExpr | Statement ) [ ";" ] ;
ExportAll   = "*" [ KwAs Id ] KwFrom StringLit ;
ExportNamed = "{" [ ExportSpec { "," ExportSpec } [ "," ] ] "}" ;
ExportSpec  = ( Id | StringLit ) [ KwAs ( Id | StringLit ) ] ;

// with, debugger, and async/generator function declarations: accepted, not lowered.
With        <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplStmt("with statement", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwWith "(" Expression ")" Statement ;
Debugger    <~~ push(notImplStmt("debugger statement", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwDebugger [ ";" ] ;
AsyncFuncDecl <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplStmt("async function", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwAsync KwFunction [ "*" ] Id ParamList Block ;
GenFuncDecl <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplStmt("generator function", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwFunction "*" Id ParamList Block ;

Null        <~~ push(makeHandleConst(1)) ~~>   = "null" KwEnd ;
Undefined   <~~ push(makeHandleConst(0)) ~~>   = "undefined" KwEnd ;

VarRef      <~~ push(makeVarRef(up.in)) ~~>
            = Id ;

StringLit   = DqString | SqString ;

// The genuine numeric literals (hex tried before decimal) plus the widened forms -
// binary, octal, BigInt and numeric separators - which are ACCEPTED but not lowered.
NumberLit   = HexLit | BinLit | OctLit | BigIntLit | SepNumLit | DecLit ;

// Hex must be tried before decimal, otherwise '0x1A' would stop after the '0'.
HexLit      <~~ push(makeConst(hexAt(up.in, 2, up.in.length - 2))) ~~>
            = ( "0x" | "0X" ) :whitespace() HexDigit { HexDigit } :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
HexDigit    = "0"..."9" | "a"..."f" | "A"..."F" ;
BinLit      <~~ push(notImplExpr("binary literal", up.pos)) ~~>
            = ( "0b" | "0B" ) :whitespace() BinDigit { BinDigit | "_" } :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
BinDigit    = "0"..."1" ;
OctLit      <~~ push(notImplExpr("octal literal", up.pos)) ~~>
            = ( "0o" | "0O" ) :whitespace() OctDigit { OctDigit | "_" } :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
OctDigit    = "0"..."7" ;
// A decimal BigInt literal ends in 'n'; tried before the plain decimal so the 'n' is
// not orphaned (a non-BigInt number fails the 'n' and rolls back to DecLit).
BigIntLit   <~~ push(notImplExpr("BigInt literal", up.pos)) ~~>
            = Digit { Digit | "_" } "n" :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
// A decimal with numeric separators (1_000, 3.141_59); requires at least one '_'.
SepNumLit   <~~ push(notImplExpr("numeric separator", up.pos)) ~~>
            = Digit { Digit } "_" { Digit | "_" } [ "." Digit { Digit | "_" } ] :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
Digit       = "0"..."9" ;

// A regular-expression literal in a primary position: /pattern/flags. A leading '/' at
// an operand position is division (handled at MulExpr), so this is only ever reached
// where a regex is genuinely valid. Accepted but not lowered (no regex engine).
RegexLit    <~~ push(notImplExpr("regular expression literal", up.pos)) ~~>
            = "/" :whitespace() RegexFirst { RegexPart } "/" { RegexFlag } :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
RegexFirst  = RegexEsc | RegexClass | RegexFirstChar ;
RegexPart   = RegexEsc | RegexClass | RegexBodyChar ;
RegexClass  = "[" { RegexEsc | RegexClassChar } "]" ;
RegexEsc    = "\\" ( "\x00"..."\x09" | "\x0b"..."\U0010ffff" ) ;
RegexFirstChar = "\x00"..."\x09" | "\x0b"..."\x29" | "\x2b"..."\x2e" | "\x30"..."\x5a" | "\x5d"..."\U0010ffff" ;
RegexBodyChar  = "\x00"..."\x09" | "\x0b"..."\x2e" | "\x30"..."\x5a" | "\x5d"..."\U0010ffff" ;
RegexClassChar = "\x00"..."\x09" | "\x0b"..."\x5b" | "\x5e"..."\U0010ffff" ;
RegexFlag   = "a"..."z" ;

// The keywords end with a negative lookahead, so that e.g. 'iffy' or 'variable' stay identifiers.
KwVar       = ( "var" | "let" | "const" ) KwEnd ;
KwFunction  = "function" KwEnd ;
KwIf        = "if" KwEnd ;
KwElse      = "else" KwEnd ;
KwWhile     = "while" KwEnd ;
KwDo        = "do" KwEnd ;
KwFor       = "for" KwEnd ;
KwReturn    = "return" KwEnd ;
KwBreak     = "break" KwEnd ;
KwContinue  = "continue" KwEnd ;
KwThrow     = "throw" KwEnd ;
KwTypeof    = "typeof" KwEnd ;
KwSwitch    = "switch" KwEnd ;
KwCase      = "case" KwEnd ;
KwDefault   = "default" KwEnd ;
KwOf        = "of" KwEnd ;
KwIn        = "in" KwEnd ;
KwTry       = "try" KwEnd ;
KwCatch     = "catch" KwEnd ;
KwFinally   = "finally" KwEnd ;
KwClass     = "class" KwEnd ;
KwExtends   = "extends" KwEnd ;
KwNew       = "new" KwEnd ;
KwSuper     = "super" KwEnd ;
KwConstructor = "constructor" KwEnd ;
KwImport    = "import" KwEnd ;
KwExport    = "export" KwEnd ;
KwFrom      = "from" KwEnd ;
KwAs        = "as" KwEnd ;
KwWith      = "with" KwEnd ;
KwDebugger  = "debugger" KwEnd ;
KwAsync     = "async" KwEnd ;
KwAwait     = "await" KwEnd ;
KwYield     = "yield" KwEnd ;
KwDelete    = "delete" KwEnd ;
KwVoid      = "void" KwEnd ;
KwInstanceof = "instanceof" KwEnd ;

// ---


:startScript(~~

    // Shared emitter machinery (module, handle constants, externs, loopStack
    // protocol, expression/statement builders); see the `core` knobs below.
    include("lib/compile-core.js")

    // takeAll empties the local stack of the current tag and returns its items in push
    // order as a plain JS array.
    // Resolves the JS string escapes (\n \t \r \0 \xNN \uNNNN, and \c for the char itself).

    // A clean compile-time abort (used by the shared notImpl helper in compile-core.js
    // for constructs that parse but cannot be lowered).
    function fail(msg) { println("js compiler error: " + msg); exit(1) }

    // ----- The emitter state -----

    var i8 = llvm.types.I8


    // The handle constants: 0 undefined, 1 null, 2 false, 3 true.

    // All js_* externals get declared on first use. Every parameter and result is i64,
    // except the string pool pointer of js_str_mem.
    // One module global per distinct string literal / name.
    // The function being built, the current scope chain handle (an SSA value), and the
    // enclosing loops (for break/continue).

    // An i1 for conditional branches: js_truthy(v) != 0.
    // ----- Expression thunks: function(block) -> {b: endBlock, v: i64 handle} -----

    function makeHandleConst(n) {
        var c = handle(n)
        return function(b) { return {b: b, v: c} }
    }
    function makeUnary(t, extName) {
        return function(b) {
            var r = t(b)
            return {b: r.b, v: callExt(r.b, extName, [r.v])}
        }
    }
    // ~v is v ^ -1 on the ToInt32 value, so it reuses the xor external.
    function makeBitNot(t) {
        return function(b) {
            var r = t(b)
            b = r.b
            return {b: b, v: callExt(b, "js_bxor", [r.v, callExt(b, "js_num_i", [handle(-1)])])}
        }
    }

    // ----- Widened-surface helpers: transparent pass-through with one operand, else
    // ACCEPTED-but-not-lowered (notImplExpr). The single-operand fast path keeps the
    // emitted IR byte-identical to the pre-widening grammar for ordinary expressions. -----
    function makeNullish(items, pos) { if (items.length == 1) return items[0]; return notImplExpr("nullish coalescing (??)", pos) }
    function makeExp(items, pos)     { if (items.length == 1) return items[0]; return notImplExpr("exponentiation (**)", pos) }
    function makeInInstanceof(items, pos) { if (items.length == 1) return items[0]; return notImplExpr("instanceof / in operator", pos) }
    // A not-lowered object property: a deterministic placeholder descriptor whose value
    // thunk is a notImplExpr (both engines emit the same placeholder key/value).
    function notImplProp(name, pos) { return makeProp(notImplExpr(name, pos), "0notImpl") }
    // A not-lowered class member: warn and push a skip marker makeClassStmt ignores.
    function notImplMember(name, pos) { notImpl(name, pos); return {skip: true} }

    binExt = {"+": "js_add", "-": "js_sub", "*": "js_mul", "/": "js_div", "%": "js_mod",
                  "==": "js_eq", "!=": "js_ne", "===": "js_seq", "!==": "js_sne",
                  "<": "js_lt", ">": "js_gt", "<=": "js_le", ">=": "js_ge",
                  "|": "js_bor", "^": "js_bxor", "&": "js_band",
                  "<<": "js_shl", ">>": "js_shr", ">>>": "js_ushr",
                  "+=": "js_add", "-=": "js_sub", "*=": "js_mul", "/=": "js_div", "%=": "js_mod"}
    wraps = {} // MetaJS numbers are not wrapped to 32 bit.

    // items = [thunk, op, thunk, op, thunk, ...] -> one left folded thunk.
    // || and && evaluate lazily and keep the deciding operand, exactly like in JS.
    // Each step branches: on a decided value the right side is skipped, a phi merges.
    // items = [thunk] or [condThunk, thenThunk, elseThunk].
    function makeCond(items) {
        if (items.length == 1) return items[0]
        return function(b) {
            var r = items[0](b)
            var thenB = curF.NewBlock("")
            var elseB = curF.NewBlock("")
            var mergeB = curF.NewBlock("")
            r.b.NewCondBr(truthy(r.b, r.v), thenB, elseB)
            var rt = items[1](thenB)
            rt.b.NewBr(mergeB)
            var re = items[2](elseB)
            re.b.NewBr(mergeB)
            var phi = mergeB.NewPhi([llvm.ir.NewIncoming(rt.v, rt.b), llvm.ir.NewIncoming(re.v, re.b)])
            return {b: mergeB, v: phi}
        }
    }

    function makeArray(items) {
        return function(b) {
            var arr = callExt(b, "js_arr_new", [])
            for (var i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
                var r = items[i](b)
                b = r.b
                callExt(b, "js_arr_push", [arr, r.v])
            }
            return {b: b, v: arr}
        }
    }
    // PropDef pops [valueThunk, key]; the key is an Id string or a constant string thunk.
    function makeProp(valT, key) {
        return {kt: (typeof key == "string") ? makeConst(key) : key, t: valT}
    }
    function makeObject(props) {
        return function(b) {
            var obj = callExt(b, "js_obj_new", [])
            for (var i = 0; i < props.length; i++) {
                var kr = props[i].kt(b)
                b = kr.b
                var vr = props[i].t(b)
                b = vr.b
                callExt(b, "js_set", [obj, kr.v, vr.v])
            }
            return {b: b, v: obj}
        }
    }

    // items = [primaryThunk, {kind:"call"|"member", ...}...]. A member access remembers
    // its object handle, so that a directly following call uses it as 'this'.
    // A member access immediately followed by a call is a method call: look the property
    // up (js_get); if it is a function value it is called directly (js_call, this = the
    // object) - that keeps every native string/array method and object-literal method
    // working exactly as before; otherwise it is a __class instance method, dispatched
    // through js_mcall (which prepends the receiver and follows __super). A call not
    // preceded by a member is a plain function call.
    foldCallMember = function(items) {
        if (items.length == 1) return items[0]
        var primary = items[0]
        var suffixes = items.slice(1)
        // Any optional-chaining suffix (?. ?.[ ?.( ) routes the whole chain to
        // notImplemented: there is no short-circuit-on-nullish model in the subset.
        for (var oi = 0; oi < suffixes.length; oi++) {
            if (suffixes[oi].kind == "optchain") return notImplExpr("optional chaining (?.)", suffixes[oi].pos)
        }
        return function(b) {
            var r = primary(b)
            b = r.b
            var cur = r.v
            var curThis = hUndef
            var i = 0
            while (i < suffixes.length) {
                var s = suffixes[i]
                if (s.kind == "member") {
                    var kr = s.key(b)
                    b = kr.b
                    if (i + 1 < suffixes.length && suffixes[i + 1].kind == "call") {
                        var callS = suffixes[i + 1]
                        var objV = cur
                        var keyV = kr.v
                        var fV = callExt(b, "js_get", [objV, keyV])
                        var argsV = callExt(b, "js_arr_new", [])
                        for (var j = 0; j < callS.args.length; j++) {
                            var ar = callS.args[j](b)
                            b = ar.b
                            callExt(b, "js_arr_push", [argsV, ar.v])
                        }
                        var isFn = truthy(b, callExt(b, "js_seq", [callExt(b, "js_typeof", [fV]), emitStr(b, "function")]))
                        var thenB = curF.NewBlock("")
                        var elseB = curF.NewBlock("")
                        var mergeB = curF.NewBlock("")
                        b.NewCondBr(isFn, thenB, elseB)
                        var tv = callExt(thenB, "js_call", [fV, objV, argsV])
                        thenB.NewBr(mergeB)
                        var ev = callExt(elseB, "js_mcall", [objV, keyV, argsV])
                        elseB.NewBr(mergeB)
                        cur = mergeB.NewPhi([llvm.ir.NewIncoming(tv, thenB), llvm.ir.NewIncoming(ev, elseB)])
                        b = mergeB
                        curThis = hUndef
                        i = i + 2
                    } else {
                        curThis = cur
                        cur = callExt(b, "js_get", [cur, kr.v])
                        i = i + 1
                    }
                } else {
                    var argsV2 = callExt(b, "js_arr_new", [])
                    for (var k = 0; k < s.args.length; k++) {
                        var ar2 = s.args[k](b)
                        b = ar2.b
                        callExt(b, "js_arr_push", [argsV2, ar2.v])
                    }
                    cur = callExt(b, "js_call", [cur, curThis, argsV2])
                    curThis = hUndef
                    i = i + 1
                }
            }
            return {b: b, v: cur}
        }
    }

    // Target items = [nameString, suffix marker...] -> reference descriptor.
    // Walks a target path (members and calls) up to the last element, which must
    // be a member. Returns {b, obj, key} with the object and the last key evaluated.
    function emitRefPath(b, ref) {
        var cur = callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, ref.name)])
        var curThis = hUndef
        for (var i = 0; i < ref.path.length - 1; i++) {
            var s = ref.path[i]
            if (s.kind == "member") {
                curThis = cur
                var kr = s.key(b)
                b = kr.b
                cur = callExt(b, "js_get", [cur, kr.v])
            } else {
                var argsV = callExt(b, "js_arr_new", [])
                for (var j = 0; j < s.args.length; j++) {
                    var ar = s.args[j](b)
                    b = ar.b
                    callExt(b, "js_arr_push", [argsV, ar.v])
                }
                cur = callExt(b, "js_call", [cur, curThis, argsV])
                curThis = hUndef
            }
        }
        var last = ref.path[ref.path.length - 1].key(b)
        return {b: last.b, obj: cur, key: last.v}
    }
    // items = [ref, opString, valueThunk]. The value of an assignment is the assigned value.
    function makeAssign(items) {
        var ref = items[0]
        var op = items[1]
        var valT = items[2]
        return function(b) {
            var r = valT(b)
            b = r.b
            var v = r.v
            if (ref.path.length == 0) {
                var nameV = emitStr(b, ref.name)
                // Plain `=` to an undeclared name becomes an implicit global
                // (js_scope_set_or_create). A compound assignment first reads the
                // old value, so it still requires a prior declaration.
                var setExt = "js_scope_set_or_create"
                if (op != "=") {
                    var old = callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, nameV])
                    v = callExt(b, binExt[op], [old, v])
                    setExt = "js_scope_set"
                }
                callExt(b, setExt, [curScopeV, nameV, v])
            } else {
                var p = emitRefPath(b, ref)
                b = p.b
                if (op != "=") {
                    var oldM = callExt(b, "js_get", [p.obj, p.key])
                    v = callExt(b, binExt[op], [oldM, v])
                }
                callExt(b, "js_set", [p.obj, p.key, v])
            }
            return {b: b, v: v}
        }
    }
    // items = [ref, "++"|"--"]. Post increment: the expression value is the old (coerced) one.
    function makeIncDec(items) {
        var ref = items[0]
        var extName = (items[1] == "++") ? "js_add" : "js_sub"
        return function(b) {
            var oneV = callExt(b, "js_num_i", [handle(1)])
            if (ref.path.length == 0) {
                var nameV = emitStr(b, ref.name)
                var oldV = callExt(b, "js_tonum", [callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, nameV])])
                callExt(b, "js_scope_set", [curScopeV, nameV, callExt(b, extName, [oldV, oneV])])
                return {b: b, v: oldV}
            }
            var p = emitRefPath(b, ref)
            b = p.b
            var oldM = callExt(b, "js_tonum", [callExt(b, "js_get", [p.obj, p.key])])
            callExt(b, "js_set", [p.obj, p.key, callExt(b, extName, [oldM, oneV])])
            return {b: b, v: oldM}
        }
    }
    // Prefix ++/--: like makeIncDec, but the expression value is the new one.
    function makePreIncDec(ref, op) {
        var extName = (op == "++") ? "js_add" : "js_sub"
        return function(b) {
            var oneV = callExt(b, "js_num_i", [handle(1)])
            if (ref.path.length == 0) {
                var nameV = emitStr(b, ref.name)
                var oldV = callExt(b, "js_tonum", [callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, nameV])])
                var newV = callExt(b, extName, [oldV, oneV])
                callExt(b, "js_scope_set", [curScopeV, nameV, newV])
                return {b: b, v: newV}
            }
            var p = emitRefPath(b, ref)
            b = p.b
            var oldM = callExt(b, "js_tonum", [callExt(b, "js_get", [p.obj, p.key])])
            var newM = callExt(b, extName, [oldM, oneV])
            callExt(b, "js_set", [p.obj, p.key, newM])
            return {b: b, v: newM}
        }
    }

    // A function body: an own IR function jsf_N(env, args) whose entry opens a scope on
    // the passed environment, binds the parameters and 'arguments', and runs the body.
    // isCtl marks a try/catch body closure: a return/break/continue leaving it emits a
    // control signal instead of a ret/br (see compile-core inCtlBody / excDispatch).
    function emitFunction(paramNames, bodyT, isCtl) {
        funcCount++
        var idx = funcCount
        var f = m.NewFunc("jsf_" + idx, i64, [llvm.ir.NewParam("env", i64), llvm.ir.NewParam("args", i64)])

        var savedF = curF
        var savedScope = curScopeV
        var savedLoops = loopStack
        var savedTag = curFTag
        curF = f
        curFTag = idx
        loopStack = []
        if (isCtl) { ctlEnter(idx) }

        var b = f.NewBlock("entry")
        curScopeV = callExt(b, "js_scope_new", [f.Params[0]])
        for (var i = 0; i < paramNames.length; i++) {
            callExt(b, "js_scope_decl", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, paramNames[i]),
                                    callExt(b, "js_arg", [f.Params[1], handle(i)])])
        }
        callExt(b, "js_scope_decl", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, "arguments"), f.Params[1]])
        var endB = bodyT(b)
        endB.NewRet(hUndef) // A function without return returns undefined.

        if (isCtl) { ctlLeave() }
        curF = savedF
        curScopeV = savedScope
        loopStack = savedLoops
        curFTag = savedTag
        return idx
    }
    function makeFunctionExpr(bodyT, paramNames) {
        return function(b) {
            var idx = emitFunction(paramNames, bodyT)
            return {b: b, v: callExt(b, "js_closure", [handle(idx), curScopeV])}
        }
    }

    // Arrow function: items = [{aparams:[names]}, {body: stmtThunk} | {ebody: exprThunk}].
    // A block body is a statement thunk; an expression body becomes 'return <expr>'.
    function makeArrow(items) {
        var params = items[0].aparams
        var bm = items[1]
        var bodyT = anytype // Either a block statement thunk or a synthesized return.
        if (bm.body != undefined) {
            bodyT = bm.body
        } else {
            var et = bm.ebody
            bodyT = function(b) { var r = et(b); r.b.NewRet(r.v); return deadBlock() }
        }
        return function(b) {
            var idx = emitFunction(params, bodyT)
            return {b: b, v: callExt(b, "js_closure", [handle(idx), curScopeV])}
        }
    }

    // Template literal: items = [{str:"chunk"} | {expr: thunk}...]. Seeding with ""
    // forces JS string coercion on every interpolated part (js_add).
    function makeTemplate(items) {
        return function(b) {
            var v = emitStr(b, "")
            for (var i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
                var pv = anytype // The chunk handle: a literal string or an expression value.
                if (items[i].str != undefined) { pv = emitStr(b, items[i].str) }
                else {
                    var r = items[i].expr(b)
                    b = r.b
                    pv = r.v
                }
                v = callExt(b, "js_add", [v, pv])
            }
            return {b: b, v: v}
        }
    }

    // for-of / for-in. items = [name, "of"|"in", iterThunk, bodyThunk].
    // for-of genuinely iterates by index over an array/string: it opens its own scope
    // holding the iterable, the length, and the index (hidden 0-prefixed names that no
    // JS identifier can collide with), then loops name = iter[i] while i < length.
    // for-in iterates the object's own keys: js_keys yields them (insertion order,
    // deterministic, __-prefixed slots skipped), and the same index loop walks that key
    // array, binding name to each key string.
    function makeForOf(items, pos) {
        var name = items[0]
        var iterT = items[2]
        var bodyT = items[3]
        var isIn = items[1] == "in"
        return function(b) {
            var saved = curScopeV
            curScopeV = callExt(b, "js_scope_new", [saved])
            var ir = iterT(b)
            b = ir.b
            var seqV = ir.v
            if (isIn) { seqV = callExt(b, "js_keys", [seqV]) }
            var lenV = callExt(b, "js_tonum", [callExt(b, "js_get", [seqV, emitStr(b, "length")])])
            callExt(b, "js_scope_decl", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, "0it"), seqV])
            callExt(b, "js_scope_decl", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, "0len"), lenV])
            callExt(b, "js_scope_decl", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, "0i"), callExt(b, "js_num_i", [handle(0)])])
            callExt(b, "js_scope_decl", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, name), hUndef])
            var headB = curF.NewBlock("")
            var bodyB = curF.NewBlock("")
            var postB = curF.NewBlock("")
            var exitB = curF.NewBlock("")
            b.NewBr(headB)
            var iC = callExt(headB, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(headB, "0i")])
            var lC = callExt(headB, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(headB, "0len")])
            headB.NewCondBr(truthy(headB, callExt(headB, "js_lt", [iC, lC])), bodyB, exitB)
            var iB = callExt(bodyB, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(bodyB, "0i")])
            var itB = callExt(bodyB, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(bodyB, "0it")])
            callExt(bodyB, "js_scope_set", [curScopeV, emitStr(bodyB, name), callExt(bodyB, "js_get", [itB, iB])])
            loopStack.push({cont: postB, brk: exitB})
            bodyT(bodyB).NewBr(postB)
            loopStack.pop()
            var iP = callExt(postB, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(postB, "0i")])
            var nextV = callExt(postB, "js_add", [iP, callExt(postB, "js_num_i", [handle(1)])])
            callExt(postB, "js_scope_set", [curScopeV, emitStr(postB, "0i"), nextV])
            postB.NewBr(headB)
            curScopeV = saved
            return exitB
        }
    }

    // A destructuring binding. makeDField turns a parsed object field into
    // {key, pat}: a shorthand {x} binds property x to a name x, {x: t} binds
    // property x to the sub-pattern t. bindPatternC walks a pattern node
    // ({dtype:"id"|"arr"|"obj"}) against a value handle, emitting js_scope_decl for
    // each leaf name; array elements are fetched by js_get with a numeric index,
    // object properties by js_get with the key string. Same tree as the interpreter.
    function makeDField(items) {
        if (items.length == 1) return {key: items[0], pat: {dtype: "id", name: items[0]}}
        return {key: items[0], pat: items[1]}
    }
    function bindPatternC(b, pat, valueH) {
        if (pat.dtype == "id") {
            callExt(b, "js_scope_decl", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, pat.name), valueH])
        } else if (pat.dtype == "arr") {
            for (var i = 0; i < pat.elems.length; i++) {
                var subA = callExt(b, "js_get", [valueH, callExt(b, "js_num_i", [handle(i)])])
                b = bindPatternC(b, pat.elems[i], subA)
            }
        } else {
            for (var j = 0; j < pat.fields.length; j++) {
                var subO = callExt(b, "js_get", [valueH, emitStr(b, pat.fields[j].key)])
                b = bindPatternC(b, pat.fields[j].pat, subO)
            }
        }
        return b
    }
    // items = [patternNode, initThunk]. Evaluate the initializer once, then bind.
    function makeDestructure(items, pos) {
        var pat = items[0]
        var init = items[1]
        return function(b) {
            var r = init(b)
            b = r.b
            b = bindPatternC(b, pat, r.v)
            return b
        }
    }

    // try/catch/finally is not implemented; under -warn the try block runs.
    // items = [name, blockThunk] or [blockThunk] (no binding).
    function makeCatch(items) {
        if (items.length > 1) { return {catchbody: items[1], catchname: items[0]} }
        return {catchbody: items[0], catchname: undefined}
    }
    // try/catch/finally: each body compiles to its own IR closure handed to js_try; the
    // try and catch bodies are ctl closures, so a return/break/continue leaving them
    // becomes a control signal that excDispatch re-issues here.
    function makeTry(items) {
        var tryT = anytype, catchT = anytype, catchName = anytype, finallyT = anytype
        for (var i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
            if (items[i].trybody != undefined) { tryT = items[i].trybody }
            else if (items[i].catchbody != undefined) { catchT = items[i].catchbody; catchName = items[i].catchname }
            else if (items[i].finbody != undefined) { finallyT = items[i].finbody }
        }
        return function(b) {
            var tryClo = callExt(b, "js_closure", [handle(emitFunction([], tryT, true)), curScopeV])
            var catchClo = hUndef
            if (catchT != undefined) {
                var cn = (catchName != undefined) ? catchName : "__caught"
                catchClo = callExt(b, "js_closure", [handle(emitFunction([cn], catchT, true)), curScopeV])
            }
            var finClo = hUndef
            if (finallyT != undefined) {
                finClo = callExt(b, "js_closure", [handle(emitFunction([], finallyT, true)), curScopeV])
            }
            var ctl = callExt(b, "js_try", [tryClo, catchClo, finClo])
            return excDispatch(b, ctl)
        }
    }

    // ----- Classes (the __class machinery) -----
    // An instance is a js_obj_new object carrying a __class descriptor; the descriptor
    // holds the methods (js_closure over the class-defining scope) and the __ctor. A
    // method call dispatches through js_mcall (which prepends the instance as the
    // receiver and follows __super for inheritance); super.m() goes through js_supercall.

    // The class whose body is being built, captured by super() / super.m() at build time.
    var curClassName = ""

    function makeMethod(items) {
        var mods = items[0].mods
        var name = items[1].mname
        var params = items[2]   // The parameter names array (from ParamList).
        var body = items[3]
        var isStatic = false
        for (var i = 0; i < mods.length; i++) { if (mods[i] == "static") { isStatic = true } }
        return {kind: "method", name: name, statik: isStatic, params: params, body: body}
    }
    function makeCtor(items) {
        return {kind: "ctor", params: items[0], body: items[1]}
    }
    function makeField(items) {
        var mods = items[0].mods
        var name = items[1].fname
        var init = items.length > 2 ? items[2] : null
        var isStatic = false
        for (var i = 0; i < mods.length; i++) { if (mods[i] == "static") { isStatic = true } }
        return {kind: "field", name: name, statik: isStatic, init: init}
    }

    // Emits one method/constructor as jsf_N(env, args). For an instance function args[0]
    // is 'this'. A constructor (initFields != null) sets the field defaults/initializers
    // at entry; a default constructor of a subclass (implicitSuper set) first runs the
    // parent constructor with no arguments.
    function emitClassFunc(params, body, isInstance, initFields, implicitSuper) {
        funcCount++
        var idx = funcCount
        var f = m.NewFunc("jsf_" + idx, i64, [llvm.ir.NewParam("env", i64), llvm.ir.NewParam("args", i64)])
        var savedF = curF
        var savedScope = curScopeV
        var savedLoops = loopStack
        curF = f
        loopStack = []
        var b = f.NewBlock("entry")
        curScopeV = callExt(b, "js_scope_new", [f.Params[0]])
        var off = 0
        if (isInstance) {
            callExt(b, "js_scope_decl", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, "this"), callExt(b, "js_arg", [f.Params[1], handle(0)])])
            off = 1
        }
        for (var i = 0; i < params.length; i++) {
            callExt(b, "js_scope_decl", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, params[i]),
                                    callExt(b, "js_arg", [f.Params[1], handle(i + off)])])
        }
        if (implicitSuper != undefined && implicitSuper != null) {
            var supCls = callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, implicitSuper)])
            var supCtor = callExt(b, "js_get", [supCls, emitStr(b, "__ctor")])
            var sargsV = callExt(b, "js_arr_new", [])
            callExt(b, "js_arr_push", [sargsV, callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, "this")])])
            callExt(b, "js_call", [supCtor, hUndef, sargsV])
        }
        if (initFields != null) {
            var thisV = callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, "this")])
            for (var k = 0; k < initFields.length; k++) {
                var fv = hUndef
                if (initFields[k].init != null && initFields[k].init != undefined) {
                    var r = initFields[k].init(b)
                    b = r.b
                    fv = r.v
                }
                callExt(b, "js_set", [thisV, emitStr(b, initFields[k].name), fv])
            }
        }
        var endB = body != null ? body(b) : b
        endB.NewRet(hUndef)
        curF = savedF
        curScopeV = savedScope
        loopStack = savedLoops
        return idx
    }

    // A class declaration: build the descriptor object, bind it in the current scope,
    // then attach static fields, the constructor and the methods.
    function makeClassStmt(items) {
        var name = items[0].cname
        var superName = null
        var members = []
        for (var i = 1; i < items.length; i++) {
            if (items[i] == undefined) { continue }
            if (items[i].ext != undefined) { superName = items[i].ext }
            else if (items[i].skip != undefined) { continue }
            else { members.push(items[i]) }
        }
        var fields = []
        var methods = []
        var statics = []
        var ctorInfo = null
        for (var j = 0; j < members.length; j++) {
            var mm = members[j]
            if (mm.kind == "field") { if (mm.statik) { statics.push(mm) } else { fields.push(mm) } }
            else if (mm.kind == "method") { methods.push(mm) }
            else if (mm.kind == "ctor") { ctorInfo = mm }
        }
        return function(b) {
            var clsV = callExt(b, "js_obj_new", [])
            callExt(b, "js_set", [clsV, emitStr(b, "__isclass"), hTrue])
            callExt(b, "js_set", [clsV, emitStr(b, "__name"), emitStr(b, name)])
            if (superName != null) {
                callExt(b, "js_set", [clsV, emitStr(b, "__super"),
                                      callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, superName)])])
            }
            callExt(b, "js_scope_decl", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, name), clsV])
            for (var s = 0; s < statics.length; s++) {
                var sv = hUndef
                if (statics[s].init != null && statics[s].init != undefined) {
                    var rs = statics[s].init(b)
                    b = rs.b
                    sv = rs.v
                }
                callExt(b, "js_set", [clsV, emitStr(b, statics[s].name), sv])
            }
            var ctorIdx
            if (ctorInfo != null) {
                ctorIdx = emitClassFunc(ctorInfo.params, ctorInfo.body, true, fields, null)
            } else {
                ctorIdx = emitClassFunc([], null, true, fields, superName)
            }
            callExt(b, "js_set", [clsV, emitStr(b, "__ctor"), callExt(b, "js_closure", [handle(ctorIdx), curScopeV])])
            for (var mi = 0; mi < methods.length; mi++) {
                var idx = emitClassFunc(methods[mi].params, methods[mi].body, !methods[mi].statik, null, null)
                callExt(b, "js_set", [clsV, emitStr(b, methods[mi].name), callExt(b, "js_closure", [handle(idx), curScopeV])])
            }
            return b
        }
    }

    // new C(args): build the instance, attach __class, run the constructor as
    // __ctor(instance, args...).
    function makeNew(items) {
        var clsName = items[0].cls
        var argThunks = items.slice(1)
        return function(b) {
            var clsV = callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, clsName)])
            var objV = callExt(b, "js_obj_new", [])
            callExt(b, "js_set", [objV, emitStr(b, "__class"), clsV])
            var argsV = callExt(b, "js_arr_new", [])
            callExt(b, "js_arr_push", [argsV, objV])
            for (var i = 0; i < argThunks.length; i++) {
                var r = argThunks[i](b)
                b = r.b
                callExt(b, "js_arr_push", [argsV, r.v])
            }
            var ctorV = callExt(b, "js_get", [clsV, emitStr(b, "__ctor")])
            callExt(b, "js_call", [ctorV, hUndef, argsV])
            return {b: b, v: objV}
        }
    }

    // super(args): delegate to the parent constructor. super.m(args): dispatch m on the
    // parent class (js_supercall walks __super from there). The defining class is
    // captured at build time (curClassName).
    function makeSuperCall(name, argThunks) {
        var defName = curClassName
        if (name == "") {
            return function(b) {
                var clsV = callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, defName)])
                var supV = callExt(b, "js_get", [clsV, emitStr(b, "__super")])
                var supCtor = callExt(b, "js_get", [supV, emitStr(b, "__ctor")])
                var thisV = callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, "this")])
                var argsV = callExt(b, "js_arr_new", [])
                callExt(b, "js_arr_push", [argsV, thisV])
                for (var i = 0; i < argThunks.length; i++) {
                    var r = argThunks[i](b)
                    b = r.b
                    callExt(b, "js_arr_push", [argsV, r.v])
                }
                callExt(b, "js_call", [supCtor, hUndef, argsV])
                return {b: b, v: hUndef}
            }
        }
        return function(b) {
            var clsV = callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, defName)])
            var supV = callExt(b, "js_get", [clsV, emitStr(b, "__super")])
            var thisV = callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, "this")])
            var argsV = callExt(b, "js_arr_new", [])
            for (var i = 0; i < argThunks.length; i++) {
                var r = argThunks[i](b)
                b = r.b
                callExt(b, "js_arr_push", [argsV, r.v])
            }
            return {b: b, v: callExt(b, "js_supercall", [supV, thisV, emitStr(b, name), argsV])}
        }
    }

    // ----- Statement thunks: function(block) -> block to continue in -----

    // An expression in statement position: evaluate the value and record it as the
    // program completion value (what a goja Run() would return; js_getret reads it).
    exprToStmt = function(t) {
        return function(b) {
            var r = t(b)
            callExt(r.b, "js_setret", [r.v])
            return r.b
        }
    }
    // For loop init/post clauses: evaluate and drop (they are no statements, so
    // they must not touch the completion value).
    function exprToClause(t) {
        return function(b) { return t(b).b }
    }
    // items = [name] or [name, initThunk].
    function makeDecl(items) {
        var name = items[0]
        return function(b) {
            var v = hUndef
            if (items.length > 1) {
                var r = items[1](b)
                b = r.b
                v = r.v
            }
            callExt(b, "js_scope_decl", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, name), v])
            return b
        }
    }
    // items = [cond, then] or [cond, then, else].
    // Note: the childs lie on the stack in source order, so pop() delivers them reversed.
    function makeDo(condT, bodyT) {
        return function(b) {
            var bodyB = curF.NewBlock("")
            var condB = curF.NewBlock("")
            var exitB = curF.NewBlock("")
            b.NewBr(bodyB)
            loopStack.push({cont: condB, brk: exitB})
            bodyT(bodyB).NewBr(condB)
            loopStack.pop()
            var r = condT(condB)
            r.b.NewCondBr(truthy(r.b, r.v), bodyB, exitB)
            return exitB
        }
    }
    // items = [{k:"init"|"cond"|"post", t:thunk}..., bodyThunk].
    function makeFor(items) {
        var bodyT = items.pop()
        var init = null, cond = null, post = null
        for (var i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
            if (items[i].k == "init") init = items[i].t
            if (items[i].k == "cond") cond = items[i].t
            if (items[i].k == "post") post = items[i].t
        }
        return function(b) {
            var saved = curScopeV
            curScopeV = callExt(b, "js_scope_new", [curScopeV]) // The for header is its own scope.
            if (init != null) b = init(b)
            var headB = curF.NewBlock("")
            var bodyB = curF.NewBlock("")
            var postB = curF.NewBlock("")
            var exitB = curF.NewBlock("")
            b.NewBr(headB)
            if (cond != null) {
                var r = cond(headB)
                r.b.NewCondBr(truthy(r.b, r.v), bodyB, exitB)
            } else {
                headB.NewBr(bodyB)
            }
            loopStack.push({cont: postB, brk: exitB})
            bodyT(bodyB).NewBr(postB)
            loopStack.pop()
            var pb = postB
            if (post != null) pb = post(postB)
            pb.NewBr(headB)
            curScopeV = saved
            return exitB
        }
    }
    // items = [] or [exprThunk].
    function makeReturn(items) {
        var t = items.length > 0 ? items[0] : null
        return function(b) {
            var v = hUndef
            if (t != null) {
                var r = t(b)
                b = r.b
                v = r.v
            }
            return retStmt(b, v) // plain ret, or a control signal when leaving a try body
        }
    }
    function makeThrow(t) {
        return function(b) {
            var r = t(b)
            callExt(r.b, "js_throw", [r.v])
            r.b.NewRet(hUndef) // Never reached: js_throw aborts on the host side.
            return deadBlock()
        }
    }
    // items = [subjThunk, ({casev}|{isdflt}|stmtThunk)...]. The flat label/statement
    // list is grouped at build time. The dispatch chain compares with js_seq (===);
    // the case bodies fall through into each other, break jumps to the exit, and
    // continue still targets the enclosing loop.
    function makeSwitch(items) {
        var subj = items[0]
        var cases = []
        var cur = null
        for (var i = 1; i < items.length; i++) {
            var p = items[i]
            if (p != undefined && (p.casev != undefined || p.isdflt != undefined)) {
                cur = {isDefault: p.isdflt != undefined, v: p.casev, body: []}
                cases.push(cur)
            } else {
                if (cur == null) {
                    println("js compiler error: switch: a statement before the first case label")
                    exit(1)
                }
                cur.body.push(p)
            }
        }
        return function(b) {
            var r = subj(b)
            b = r.b
            var exitB = curF.NewBlock("")
            var bodyBs = []
            var dfltB = exitB
            for (var i = 0; i < cases.length; i++) {
                bodyBs.push(curF.NewBlock(""))
                if (cases[i].isDefault && dfltB === exitB) { dfltB = bodyBs[i] }
            }
            for (var i = 0; i < cases.length; i++) {
                if (cases[i].isDefault) { continue }
                var rc = cases[i].v(b)
                b = rc.b
                var nextB = curF.NewBlock("")
                b.NewCondBr(truthy(b, callExt(b, "js_seq", [r.v, rc.v])), bodyBs[i], nextB)
                b = nextB
            }
            b.NewBr(dfltB)
            var outerCont = loopStack.length > 0 ? loopStack[loopStack.length - 1].cont : null
            loopStack.push({cont: outerCont, brk: exitB})
            for (var i = 0; i < cases.length; i++) {
                var bb = bodyBs[i]
                var body = cases[i].body
                for (var j = 0; j < body.length; j++) { bb = body[j](bb) }
                bb.NewBr(i + 1 < cases.length ? bodyBs[i + 1] : exitB)
            }
            loopStack.pop()
            return exitB
        }
    }
    // Local stack = [name, [paramNames...], bodyThunk] -- declares the closure when executed.
    function makeFuncDecl(bodyT, paramNames, name) {
        return function(b) {
            var idx = emitFunction(paramNames, bodyT)
            var cl = callExt(b, "js_closure", [handle(idx), curScopeV])
            callExt(b, "js_scope_decl", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, name), cl])
            return b
        }
    }

    // The top level statements become jsrun(scope, args): the caller provides the scope
    // that the top level declarations land in (the frozen tag executor passes the shared
    // scope of the compile run, so scripts see each others globals). The return value is
    // the completion value: what the last executed expression statement produced.
    // jsmain(env, args) is the standalone entry on top of it: it makes a fresh scope,
    // runs the program, and then calls main() - the self checking test convention.
    function buildMain(items) {
        var f = m.NewFunc("jsrun", i64, [llvm.ir.NewParam("scope", i64), llvm.ir.NewParam("args", i64)])
        curF = f
        var b = f.NewBlock("entry")
        curScopeV = f.Params[0]
        callExt(b, "js_setret", [hUndef]) // A program without expression statements completes with undefined.
        b = makeSeq(items)(b)
        b.NewRet(callExt(b, "js_getret", []))

        var fm = m.NewFunc("jsmain", i64, [llvm.ir.NewParam("env", i64), llvm.ir.NewParam("args", i64)])
        curF = fm
        var bm = fm.NewBlock("entry")
        var sc = callExt(bm, "js_scope_new", [fm.Params[0]])
        bm.NewCall(f, [sc, fm.Params[1]])
        var mainV = callExt(bm, "js_scope_get", [sc, emitStr(bm, "main")])
        var argsV = callExt(bm, "js_arr_new", [])
        bm.NewRet(callExt(bm, "js_call", [mainV, hUndef, argsV]))
    }

    // ===== goja driver =====
    // Everything below this marker is the driver for the normal (goja) run of this
    // grammar. The freezer (-freeze) cuts the start script here: only the library above
    // goes into the bootstrap snapshot; in frozen mode the Go core replaces the driver.

    // Build the module out of the parsed program.
    c.compile(c.asg)

    // Show the compiler output (the LLVM IR module).
    println(m)

    // Run jsmain() with the built-in IR interpreter and the MetaJS handle runtime.
    // The exit code of this metacompiler run is what main() returned, so test
    // programs are self checking.
    var res = llvm.RunJS(m, "jsmain")
    println("js compiler: main() returned " + res.Ret)
    exit(res.Ret)

~~) ;
